knowledge_graph.title: Hummus
knowledge_graph.description: Hummus, also spelled hommus or houmous, is a Middle Eastern dip, spread, or savory dish made from cooked, mashed chickpeas blended with tahini, lemon juice, and garlic. The standard garnish in the Middle East includes olive oil, a few whole chickpeas, parsley, and paprika.

related_questions.question: How healthy is hummus for you?
related_questions.snippet: Hummus is a versatile ingredient and a good source of fiber, along with vitamins and minerals like manganese, copper, folate, and iron. Thanks to its impressive nutrient profile, it may help ease inflammation, promote heart health, and support blood sugar management.
related_questions.title: Is Hummus Healthy? Top 8 Benefits of Hummus - Healthline

related_questions.question: What is hummus made of?
related_questions.snippet: Hummus is a smooth and creamy puree of cooked chickpeas (garbanzo beans), tahini and an acid, typically lemon juice. While hummus usually has garlic now, centuries ago it did not. Olive oil isn't a requirement either, but most modern recipes list it as an ingredient.
related_questions.title: What Is Hummus, and How Do You Make It? - Food Network

related_questions.question: Is hummus good or bad carbs?
related_questions.snippet: Simply put, hummus is a wise food choice, whether you're looking to eat a more nourishing diet, or lose weight. It's not fattening in the right quantities, and it's a great source of complex carbohydrates, protein, and fiber that your body needs to be balanced!

buttons.subtitle: Hummus Healthy Food
buttons.title: What Happens to Your Body When You Eat Hummus Regularly
buttons.snippet: It's a nutrient-rich choice to have regularly. Hummus contains both protein and carbohydrates. Per 2-tablespoon serving, it provides 5 grams of carbohydrates and 2 grams of plant-based protein. This combo makes it a well-rounded and balanced food choice.

buttons.subtitle: What Does Hummus Taste Like?
buttons.title: The Best Hummus - Cookie and Kate
buttons.snippet: The best hummus is lusciously creamy, yet somehow light and fluffy. It's beautifully smooth and swirled, and begging to be scooped up onto a wedge of pita bread. It's nutty and tangy, thanks to the tahini, with notes of bright, fresh lemon and mellow garlic.
